Dear Pybind11 developers, i noticed that in situation when hierarchy of classes if partially bound (case when most derived classes is not bound) types reported in Python seems wrong. 

For example when dealing with derived classes the base class type of hierarchy will be reported while the most derived type seems like a better (most useful) answer. Could this fixed?

Use case for this will be situation when Python bindings provided for some base library levels while objects created come from extra library level when new, derived classes is created for already bound classes.

Thanks,

```C++
#include <pybind11/pybind11.h>

struct A
{
	virtual ~A() {}

	virtual void foo() {}
};

struct B : public A
{
	void foo() override {}

	virtual void bar() {}
};


struct C : public B
{
	void foo() override {}

	void bar() override {}
};


A * get() { return new C(); }

namespace py = pybind11;

PYBIND11_MODULE(example, m)
{
	py::class_<A> (m, "A")
        .def(py::init<>())
		.def("foo", &A::foo)
		;

	py::class_<B, A> (m, "B")
        .def(py::init<>())
		.def("foo", &B::foo)
		.def("bar", &B::bar)
		;

	m.def("get", &get);
}
```

